# Trivy ignore file.
#
# The four advisories below all map to undici@6.26.0, bundled inside the npm CLI
# tarball (npm -> node-gyp -> undici). It reaches package-lock.json only via the
# dev/release-only semantic-release toolchain and is NOT in the runtime Docker
# image (the production stage removes the npm CLI entirely). The bundled copy
# cannot be lifted by package overrides and no patched npm release exists yet
# (node-gyp still requires undici ^6.25.0).
#
# Mirrors the suppression in audit-ci.json (allowlist) and .github/dependabot.yml
# (ignore). Remove all three once `npm ls undici` shows no 6.26.0 — i.e. npm ships
# a bundle with undici >= 6.27.0.
CVE-2026-12151
CVE-2026-9679
CVE-2026-11525
